The game sends analytical data back to Sega on a regular basis, which I found annoying but is stated in the Privacy Policy below.  On my phone however this process is failing and causing the application to crash at totally random times (when I am not playing the game), almost on a daily basis.  I already feel uncomfortable about Sega collecting data about me, but to botch the process really rubs salt in the wound!  Beware if privacy issues concern you. On my HTC sensation it's not full screen for some reason and the images are a little low in quality for my taste however the gameplay and sound (esp the music) is top notch.  This is a simple and addictive little game with lots of hidden little things (missions and unlockables for one), ignore the option to purchase in game and simply work for the items for now (not sure why that options there for a pay game this should be a free app if you're going the "in game purchase" route SEGA!).  Just a quick few mins on this is enough to get an idea of the overall quality and it is good for a 'bounce platforms to climb higher' game.  So if your a sonic fan you'll like it anyway, if not then I'd recommend it but be very aware of what you are buying as it's not going to be for everyone.
